    "updated_at": "2012-08-01T17:26:56Z",
    "body": "If the implementation is outside of the translation unit it'll only guess as to where it might be, and currently only looks for a file with the name of the header but with extensions [\"cpp\", \"c\", \"cc\", \"m\", \"mm\"] in the same folder as the header is in.\n\nFor projects or folders opened in Sublime Text 2 there might be a way to get all the file names in the project (as used by the goto anything feature) so a smarter way to handle this would be to find a matching implementation file that way.\n\nI'm unlikely to do anything about this myself in the near term, but have a look in sublimeclang.py around [line 204](https://github.com/quarnster/SublimeClang/blob/master/sublimeclang.py#L204) to see what it's currently doing, and feel free to submit a pull request."
